Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Uniform Distribution Solution for MS", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"60140270-c5a9-4d5e-8c03-0d166e09e908"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Look at 500 ASVs with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Epsilon]", "i"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0f382936-9afd-48d4-92a7-f1feccef5abc"],
 " chosen from a  uniform distribution.  Note, each time this notebook is \
run, a new distribution will be generated.  If you want to use the same \
distribution, make sure to save it (the one used for the manuscript is given \
below)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6df472e2-4e1e-40d9-9b6e-0866eee99212"],

Cell["Parameters use for simulations", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e19207c8-b06f-4b57-82cc-5f6063c6266e"],

Cell["\<\
Notes from Exp 1 state: \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Air feed rate to MC1 and MC2 \
reduced from 20 sccm to 10 sccm (0 \[Degree]C, 1 atm) (15 : 30 2 - Nov - \
2018, t = 3.65 d)\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], but just run the gas feed rate \
constant at 10 sccm for the simulations as the 20 sccm was only run for a \
short time.
Also, the feed O2 was measured at 20.97 for the first 3.73 days, then either \
a new air tank was installed or the old one remeasured (probably the former), \
but that increased the O2 in the feed gas to 21.06, so just use the later for \
the whole simulation.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5ac875fe-3053-4bf0-9e45-13ad4bcf96d1"],

